column5: Thanks Rob.. be no surprise.. it's been in Lake Temagami for over a decade. Only seems to be an issue when running baits below 70 feet.
100lbs flee flicker line and my old pen 209.  No serious. Nasty little buggers.
Those Globalization Fools from the G20 should have just gone to Nippissing and protested the spiny water flea.
